INT. COZY COFFEE SHOP - MORNING

The coffee shop is bustling with activity. The sound of the espresso machine humming, cups clinking, and soft chatter fills the air. The decor is warm and inviting with cushioned chairs and wooden tables. 

SARAH, an enthusiastic barista in her mid-20s, is behind the counter, grinning as she takes orders. JASON, a slightly frazzled businessman in his 30s, stands at the front of the line, glancing at his watch impatiently.

SARAH
(cheerfully)
Good morning! What can I get for you today?

JASON
(rushed)
I need a large coffee, black. And make it quick, please.

SARAH
(winking)
You got it! One large Jack Black coming right up!

Jason frowns, momentarily confused, but shakes it off.

JASON
Whatever, just hurry.

Sarah turns and starts preparing the coffee. Meanwhile, LUCY, a regular customer in her late 20s, enters the shop with a mischievous grin. She spots Jason and decides to have some fun.

LUCY
(smirking)
Hey, Jason! Fancy seeing you here. What are you ordering? A Jack Black?

JASON
(irritated)
No, just a coffee. Black.

Lucy stifles a laugh as Sarah returns with a cup.

SARAH
(cheerfully)
Here you go! One large Jack Black!

Jason takes the cup and stares at the label, which reads "Jack Black." His confusion deepens.

JASON
(annoyed)
What is this? I said black coffee, not Jack Black!

SARAH
(slightly confused)
But you said Jack Black, didn’t you?

LUCY
(teasing)
Oh, come on, Jason. Don’t you know? Jack Black is the new black coffee!

Jason looks at both women, utterly perplexed.

JASON
(raising an eyebrow)
Is this some kind of joke?

SARAH
(realizing)
Oh no! I thought you were in on it. We've been naming coffee orders after celebrities this week. It’s just regular black coffee, I promise!

Jason finally starts to see the humor and chuckles.

JASON
(shaking his head)
Alright, you got me. Next time, I’ll ask for a Dwayne "The Rock" Johnson.

Lucy and Sarah burst into laughter.

SARAH
(laughing)
Deal! Have a great day, Jason!

Jason takes a sip of his "Jack Black" and heads out the door, a smile on his face.

FADE OUT.

INT. COZY COFFEE SHOP - MORNING

The coffee shop is bustling with morning customers. The barista, JANE, a cheerful woman in her late 20s, is behind the counter taking orders. MIKE, a slightly awkward but well-meaning man in his early 30s, steps up to the counter.

MIKE
(looking at the menu)
Um, can I get a large cappuccino?

JANE
(scribbling on the cup)
Sure thing! Name for the order?

MIKE
Mike.

JANE
(writing it down)
Alright, Mike. That'll be $4.50.

MIKE
(handing over cash)
Thanks.

As Mike waits, he notices a woman, LUCY, in her late 20s, sitting at a nearby table with a small dog in a tote bag. The dog is yapping quietly.

MIKE
(to Lucy)
Cute dog! What's his name?

LUCY
(smiling)
Thanks! His name is Cappuccino.

MIKE
(laughs)
Oh, like my drink!

LUCY
(confused)
Your drink?

Just then, Jane calls out from behind the counter.

JANE
(holding up a cup)
Cappuccino for Mike!

MIKE
(to Lucy, chuckling)
See? That's my drink.

LUCY
(realizing the mix-up)
Oh, I thought you meant my dog!

MIKE
(laughing)
Well, now I feel like I should name my coffee "Dog" or something.

LUCY
(giggling)
Sure, why not? My dog would probably love the attention.

Mike grabs his coffee and heads towards the door but then stops and turns back.

MIKE
(to Lucy)
Hey, would you and Cappuccino like to join me for a walk?

LUCY
(smiling)
We'd love to. Let's go, Cappuccino!

They leave the coffee shop together, laughing about the mix-up.

FADE OUT.

INT. COFFEE SHOP - MORNING

The coffee shop is buzzing with morning activity. The aroma of freshly brewed coffee fills the air. At the counter, a barista, JANE (mid-20s), is busy taking orders. In walks SAM (30s), looking slightly confused but determined.

SAM: (approaching the counter) Hi, I’d like a tall, hot blonde, please.

JANE: (to Sam) You new in town?

SAM: (relaxed) Yeah, just moved here for a new job.

JANE: (smiling) Well, welcome! Here’s your tall, hot blonde.

SAM: (confused) Wait, this is coffee.

JANE: (grinning) Yup, that’s what you ordered.

SAM: (realization dawning) Oh no! I meant the blonde roast coffee! Not... not a blonde person!

The scene ends with everyone laughing and Joe finally getting the orders right. The coffee shop continues its lively buzz, now with a lighter, more cheerful atmosphere.

INT. SPACE STATION OBSERVATION DECK - NIGHT

The observation deck is a high-tech, sleek room with a panoramic view of the cosmos. Stars twinkle in the vast expanse, and a mysterious glowing object approaches slowly from the distance.

COMMANDER LENA HAWKINS, a seasoned astronaut in her 40s, stands by the large window, staring intently at the approaching object. Beside her is DR. EMILIO SANTOS, a brilliant but nervous xenobiologist in his 30s.

          (telepathically)
